title: Welcome
text: Taib Biygautane is a second-year doctoral student in political science at the University of Maryland (UMD). Prior to joining UMD, he pursued graduate-level coursework in International Conflict Management at Kennesaw State University and non-degree graduate courses in International Affairs at Georgia Tech. Biygautaneâ€™s research interests include the politics of foreign direct investment (FDI) and investor perceptions, the role of heads of states and their attributes in international politics, and public opinion.
